      <abstract>
        <p>World Trade Organization, bogged down by bickering over who will be named chairman of talks on freer agricultural trade, has resolved issue by appointing Peru's trade representative, Jorge Voto-Bernales; he is chosen because his country is not allied with either of rival factions, which have disagreed over free trade and protectionism (S)</p>
