    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The World Trade Organization, bogged down by bickering over who would be named the chairman of talks on promoting freer agricultural trade, has resolved the issue by appointing Peru's trade representative, Jorge Voto-Bernales. He was chosen because his country is not allied with either of the rival factions, which have disagreed over free trade and protectionism, delegates to the 136-nation organization said.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
